Both files are written. Summary:

**`transcript.json`** — 15 iterations, 64 hypotheses, 67 analyses, schema-valid.

**`analysis_summary.txt`** — narrative synthesis.

**Headline finding:** the only clinically meaningful treatment effect in the dataset is **sotorasib in KRAS-G12C–mutated, BRCA2-wildtype, MALE patients** (β ≈ +4.6 months PFS, p ≈ 0). Within KRAS-G12C+ females, sotorasib has zero effect (β ≈ -0.01); within KRAS-G12C+/BRCA2+ patients, the benefit is also abolished (interaction β = -2.55, p ≈ 2e-10). The 3-way `treatment_sotorasib × kras_g12c × sex_female` interaction is highly significant.

The other three biomarker-targeted pairs (osimertinib + EGFR, olaparib + BRCA2, pembrolizumab + PDL1/TMB) all showed null PFS effects in this cohort, confirmed via main-effects, biomarker-restricted, multivariable-adjusted, monotherapy-restricted, full interaction screen, and tree-based subgroup discovery analyses.
